API Server

GET   /api/token  send username/password, get auth token
POST  /api/users  Creates a new user with username/password
GET   /api/users/<id>  Retrieves the user with id <id>
GET   /api/resource  Retrieves example resource, requires authentication


# Register a user
$ curl -i -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"username":"test_user","password":"test_password"}' http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/users

# Get a resource with username/password
$ curl -u test_user:test_password -i -X GET http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/resource

# Get an auth token
$ curl -u test_user:test_password -i -X GET http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/token

# Get resource using retrieved token, token value is sent in username field, password is unused so can be anything
$ curl -u token_value:unused -i -X GET http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/resource


